		<tr valign=top>
			<td class="BoardRowB" colspan=2 width="83%">
				An Open Letter to Verant: <br>  <br> The new Lucin graphic for plate breastplates (including Warrior crafted, Fine Plate, and Chiton Protectors, etc.) is just plain UGLY on haflings! <br> The old look was MUCH better! Please! Now Banded tunics looks better than my warrior crafted BP! <br>  <br> Before and after shots of Crafted BP on a hafling:  <a class=BoardRowBLink target="_blank" href="http://www.worlddomination.net/eqteam/gallery/?image=140">http://www.worlddomination.net/eqteam/gallery/?image=140</a>  (new is on the right) <br>  <br> Before and after shots of Chiton Protector on a hafling:  <a class=BoardRowBLink target="_blank" href="http://www.worlddomination.net/eqteam/gallery/?image=141">http://www.worlddomination.net/eqteam/gallery/?image=141</a>  (new is on the left) <br>  <br> Please put some detailing onto the BP graphic so it doesn't look like a baggy saggy old sweatshirt! The new BPs look like Dr. Zoiberg (from Futurama)'s lobster shell. It is especially horrible on a hafling. Very wierd shaped and no detail, etching, etc. at all on it. Where did my womanly shape go? <br>  <br> The crafted shoulders, gloves, boots, all look good. <br>  <br> All of the other new mob, face, clothing graphics (especially ROBES!) look AWESOME, keep up the good work. My Erudite Wizardess is especially pleased. <br>  <br> But please please revisit the plate BP look ASAP. I think Warriors (and others who wear plate) got the short end of the stick here, and I am guessing I'm not alone in prefering the old look (very nice scrollwork on the BP) to the new look (baggy sweatshirt). <br>  <br> Please post on the official everquest developers board if you would like to see this graphic improved. The web address is  <a class=BoardRowBLink target="_blank" href="http://boards.station.sony.co">http://boards.station.sony.co</a>  m/ubb/everquest/cgi-bin/forumdisplay.cgi?action=topics&amp;forum=Developer|APO|s+Corner&amp;number=1&amp;DaysPrune=20&am p;LastLogin=  <br>  <br> Thanks, <br>  <br> Obon Took of Amazons <br> 33 Hafling Warrior <br> Vallon Zek <br>  <br> *edit* After looking more closely at the screenshots provided by Eurtha Mudtoes at  <a class=BoardRowBLink target="_blank" href="http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=get_topic&amp;f=2&amp;t=002336,">http://forums.castersrealm.com/cgi-bin/eq/ultimatebb.cgi?ubb=get_topic&amp;f=2&amp;t=002336,</a>  I agree that much of the problem is with the hafling female model itself. It is a cruddy cross between dwarf and elf, totally out of proportion. If you look at before and after pictures, who could honestly say the new models look better? The old one had more style, distiction, shading, proportion, grace of movement, etc. And I LOVED our skirts!! Back to the drawing board, please!*  <br> 		

			</td>
